sentences: John Burk (born January 6, 1962) is a record producer and co-founder of the American record label Concord Records.
In 1995 Glen Barros and John Burk co-founded Concord Records.
The album Genius Loves Company, performed by Ray Charles and produced by Burk, won the Album of the Year and Record of the Year categories at the Grammy Awards in 2005.
